OL,4,CEasington mining disaster remembered 70
OL,5,Cyears on
OL,6, A pit disaster in which dozens of
OL,7, miners died is being commemorated on
OL,8, its 70th anniversary.
OL,10,FAn underground explosion at Easington
OL,11,FColliery, County Durham, claimed the
OL,12,Flives of 81 miners and two rescue
OL,13,Fworkers on 29 May 1951.
OL,15,FA service will take place in the
OL,16,Fvillage's community garden and two
OL,17,Fmemorial benches will be unveiled.
OL,19,FThe miners' banner will then be taken
OL,20,Fto the cemetery, where wreathes will be
OL,21,Flaid at the mass grave site.
